# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Vite + React project by fixing the existing Analytics component implementation to use the correct framework-specific import and placement.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **frontend/src/App.jsx**
  - Fixed Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/next` to `@vercel/analytics/react` (correct for Vite/React projects)
  - Moved Analytics component outside of `<Routes>` to proper placement at root level
  - Wrapped Routes and Analytics in React Fragment for proper structure

## Implementation Details

The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already installed in the project, but was incorrectly configured:

**Previous Implementation (Incorrect):**
- Used Next.js import path (`@vercel/analytics/next`)
- Analytics component placed inside `<Routes>` component

**Current Implementation (Correct):**
- Uses React import path (`@vercel/analytics/react`) as per official Vercel documentation
- Analytics component placed at root level alongside Routes
- Follows official quickstart guide from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ Fetched latest installation instructions from official Vercel documentation
2. ✅ Identified framework (Vite + React) and applied correct framework-specific configuration
3. ✅ Updated Analytics import to use `@vercel/analytics/react`
4. ✅ Moved Analytics component to proper root-level placement
5. ✅ Installed dependencies using npm (project's package manager)
6. ✅ Verified build completes successfully (`npm run build` passed)
7. ✅ Confirmed no linter errors (no linter configured in this project)
8. ✅ Confirmed no test failures (no tests configured in this project)

## How to Verify

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Navigate to your Vercel dashboard
2. Select Analytics in the sidebar
3. Choose this project
4. Click "Enable" button if not already enabled
5. Visit your deployed site and check browser Network tab for Fetch/XHR request from `/<unique-path>/view`

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals
- Analytics data will appear in the Vercel dashboard after user visits accumulate
- The implementation follows official Vercel best practices for React/Vite applications
